-- compiler2 wall repro: ONE-USER-ENUM LIMIT (sample-rung-walls.md).
-- enter_enum_decl (compiler2/driver.ev) requires (¬_user_enum_done),
-- so this SECOND enum decl cannot enter the variant walk. With the
-- loud guard it halts Exit(9); before, the decl was silently dropped
-- and QWrap/QNone resolved to 0 handles at first use. sample.ev has
-- 31 enums — this is its primary compile blocker (2026-06-10).
-- entry: main
-- expect: exit = 9 (compiler2 today; 0 once the multi-enum registry lands)
enum QOp = QPlus | QMinus
enum QW = QWrap(QOp) | QNone
claim main
    t ∈ QW = QWrap(QPlus)
    ok ∈ Bool = (t matches QWrap(_))
